name: NBA
summary: The 2023 NBA Finals continue to heat up, with the Dallas Mavericks forcing a Game 5 after a nail-biting Game 4. The Boston Celtics, however, maintain a 3-1 lead after a 105-98 victory in Game 2. Despite these setbacks, the Mavericks and their young star Luka Doncic have impressed in their first NBA Finals appearance. Meanwhile, the league mourns the loss of Jerry West, the legendary NBA player and inspiration for the league's iconic logo. In other news, the NBA announces the return of the Mexico City Games in 2024, while fans eagerly await Game 4 of the Celtics-Mavericks series, which has been the most-watched NBA Finals Game 2 in five years.
